critical_positive: What worked well about this  conversation is that I think we both came in ready to make the conversation work. This is my fourth conversation and I am always kind of leery about the partner I may get, but so far it has been good because the other person has had the same goal in mind to make the conversation work as best as possible, I believe.

critical_positive: I really enjoyed how my partner was very friendly. She was very polite and receptive to what I was saying. She asked questions to learn more about the topic we were talking about. Because we both live in different areas, we both asked each other questions about where we lived and what it was like. I felt that that the conversation did not feel like I was talking to a complete stranger.
critical_negative: What did not work well with the conversation was that we did not ask each other more personal questions to learn more about each other. The majority of the topic that we talked about was about Covid; Although the conversation was interesting, I felt that our topic was not particularly unique. The topic of the conversation was very general and can be had with anyone. We could have talked a little bit more about our personal lives ex: hobbies, worst fears etc. In the end, I felt like I did not learn more about her life.
